  "text": "The diagnosis of primary BC and histopathological analysis were performed using tissue samples obtained by a tru-cut or fineneedle aspiration biopsy before the PET/CT examinations. Nuclear grade and histological type were determined using formalin-fixed and paraffin-embedded 5 mm tumor tissue sections stained with haematoxylin and eosin. The ER and PR were considered positive if tumors showed moderate or high positivity (2 or 3+) for at least 10% of the tumor cells assessed using ER and PR antibodies. The HER2 status was considered positive when the membrane immunostaining was 3+ or when it was 2+ and HER2 gene amplification was present according to fluorescence in-situ hybridization analysis. For the Ki-67 expression, the percentage of positively nuclear-stained cells was determined and counted according to the recommendations of the international Ki-67 in BC Working Group. The Scarff Bloom Richardson classification system was utilized for histopathological staging. [CITATION_1] The subtypes of BC were defined according to the recommendations of the 12 th International Breast Conference, and immunohistochemical surrogates were as follows [CITATION_2] :",
